title: Walt Disney World 1979 archive footage
description:
Archival footage shot by an amateur filmmaker while visiting Orlando, Florida, probably in 1979

It contains stock footage of Walt Disney World Resort: visitors walking in the streets of the theme park, the character parades with Mickey Mouse leading the Walt Disney World Band on the parade route, visitors walking in front of Cinderella Castle, and more.

Please, comment if you recognize more subjects.

title: Putin’s war sparks Russian gas headache for the West; China tells EU Nation to abandon sanctions
description:
It is difficult for the U.S.-led West, which has preached the world to stay away from Russian energy amid Ukraine war, to ditch Russian gas itself. Currently, there are no sanctions on import of Russian Liquified Natural Gas (LNG) and hence many European Union nations continue to supply it. President Vladimir Putin's ally and counterpart Xi Jinping met with the PM of Spain, which is the leading importer of Russian gas. He urged the western nations to abandon sanctions' mentality for peace between Russia and Ukraine. Watch this video for more details.

title: Judge Luttig: 'No end in sight' on democracy perils
description:
Judge J. Michael Luttig, the former Federal Appeals judge for the Fourth Circuit, helped prevent Donald Trump from overturning the election on January 6th 2021 with a series of tweets. He’s since been outspoken about the perils facing our democracy. With the news of Trump’s indictment members of the GOP are “circling of the wagons to protect the former president,” said Judge Luttig. “Their now unified and continuing insistence that the former president won the 2020 presidential election, and that January 6 was nothing to be concerned about.” Now, As we watch the GOP abandon all pretense of operating under the rule of law - of operating with democratic values - this conversation feels more prescient than ever.

description:

The AQIS magazine claimed that Muslims in India are being persecuted, citing bulldozer action, Hijab row and mob violence to base its charge and accused the Government at the Centre of spearheading the anti-Muslim campaign. The terrorist group in its message to Pakistani Muslims urged them to rise and support Indian Muslims. The AQIS also invoked the release of Indian fighter pilot Abhinandan in 2019 to slam Pakistani Govt and Army and accused them of 'abandoning' Muslims and militancy in Kashmir. description: The twisted minds of two of the six screenwriters behind Scary Movie -- Aaron Seltzer and Jason Friedberg -- this time skewer the romantic comedy genre. But before they can have their Big Fat Greek Wedding, they'll have to Meet the Parents, hook-up with The Wedding Planner, and contend with Grant's friend Andy -- a spectacularly beautiful woman who wants to put an end to her Best Friend's Wedding.

In Russia, it is mandatory for men aged between 18 and 27 to carry out one year of military service.

title: LOSTPLACE // VERLASSENE WELTRAUMSTATION 🚀gefunden 😱 TELESKOPE zurückgelassen! 🔭
description:
💯-% KOSTENLOS den Kanal abonnieren ▶︎https://www.youtube.com/losthistorie 

Die verlassene Weltraumschule, ja ihr habt richtig gehört! So einen Lostplace gab es auf YouTube noch nie. Wir fanden in diese verlassene Location zwei uralte Teleskope 🔭, versteckt in den Kuppeln 🚀, dieses Architektur mäßigem Meisterwerkes 🏛️. Das Observatorium wurde 1882 errichtet und die Arbeits und Forschungsschwerpunkte waren die Positionsbestimmung von Sternen ⭐, die Messung des irdischen Magnetfeldes 🧲 und die Spektroskopie. Während unserer Erkunden 🔦 waren wir einfach nur beeindruckt von dem natürlichem Verfall und den hinterlassenen Teleskopen🔭. Nachher stellte sich heraus, dass es sich um eine Schule Handeln muss, wieso wurde diese Schule 🏫 aufgegeben, wieso ist sie mittlerweile dem Verfall 🏚️ ausgesetzt worden? Doch ganz unbewacht 👮‍♀️ ist diese Location nicht und wir mussten bei unserer Erkundung extrem vorsichtig sein ... ⚠️

LOST PLACES - Verlassene Orte - NRW - Deutschland - Europa 

Kanalmitglied werden und exklusive Vorteile erhalten:
https://www.youtube.com/channel/UChzqZBVbkC06bwJ5dHHqyag/join

Auf meinem Kanal befasse ich mich mit dem Thema Urban Exploring. 
(kurz: Urbex/Urbexing)
Urban Exploring ist die "private" Erkundung von Einrichtungen und sogenannten "Lost Places".
Seit 2015 besichtige ich verlassene Industrieanlagen, Katakomben, Bunker, Krankenhäuser, Villen, Industrieruinen, Militärische Anlagen, Bildungseinrichtungen und vieles mehr. 
In dieser Szene wird sich an gewisse Regeln wie z.B: 
"Take nothing but pictures, leave nothing but foodprints" gehalten. 
Uns inspiriert der Verfall der verlassenen Gebäude und die dazugehörige Geschichte.
Nun möchten wir euch auf unsere Reise gerne mitnehmen und unsere Abenteuer mit euch teilen.

What is the Khalistan movement and why is it making headlines again? In this video, we will explain the history and the current situation of the Sikh separatist movement that seeks to create a sovereign state called Khalistan in the Punjab region. We will also talk about Amritpal Singh, a radical leader who has been on the run from Indian authorities since February 2023, and how his popularity has sparked protests and violence in India and abroad. Watch this video to learn more about the Khalistan movement and its implications for India’s security and stability.

#abhiandniyu #khalistan 

Who is Amritpal Singh?

Amritpal Singh is a radical Sikh separatist leader who heads a group called Waris Punjab De, which supports the Khalistan movement. He has been on the run from Indian authorities since March 18, 2023, after he escaped a police raid in Jalandhar. He has a large following on social media and has called for a Sarbat Khalsa, a congregation of Sikhs, to discuss issues concerning the Sikh community. His popularity and calls for a separate Sikh nation have sparked protests and violence in India and abroad

What is the Khalistan Movement?

The Khalistan movement is a Sikh separatist movement seeking to create a homeland for Sikhs by establishing a sovereign state called Khalistan in the Punjab region1 The movement began in the wake of the fall of the British Empire and gained momentum in the 1970s and 1980s with the support of the Sikh diaspora The movement reached its peak in 1984, when the Indian Army stormed the Golden Temple, the holiest shrine of Sikhs, to flush out militant leader Jarnail Singh Bhindranwale, who was killed in the operation The same year, Prime Minister Indira Gandhi was assassinated by her Sikh bodyguards, sparking anti-Sikh riots that killed thousands of Sikhs across India. The movement declined in the 1990s due to a heavy police crackdown, factional infighting, and loss of public support1 However, there is still some support for the movement within India and among the Sikh diaspora, especially in the UK, Canada, and Australia The movement advocates for a separate state with varying boundaries, some including parts of Pakistan and other Indian states The movement also has a proposed flag and a capital city

description:
Welcome to the #15 episode of the Truth Hurts Podcast, today we will be talking about Merging the Masters with Modern Street Art with Isaac Pelayo.
•••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••

In this 15th episode of Truth Hurts podcast, join us for an inspiring conversation with talented artist Isaac Pelayo as we discuss his unique blend of classical and modern art styles. Delve into Isaac's artistic journey, from his beginnings with pencil sketches to mastering oil painting and spray paint, and uncover how masters like Da Vinci, Caravaggio, and Rembrandt have influenced his work. We'll also explore thought-provoking topics such as reincarnation, evolving perspectives on sexuality in art, and the crucial role the Medici family played in the Renaissance period. Alongside personal experiences with art and travel, Isaac shares his motivations for creating, his dedication to self-fulfillment, and his multifaceted artistic pursuits.

title: Waking Up Free: India’s Journey Produced By Silambam
description:
This exquisite dance tells the stories of India’s struggle for independence, and celebrates her heroes, through the dynamic kaleidoscope of dance, in this, the 75th year of Indian Independence. Based on the traditional Maargam format of Bharatanatyam, this original production will weave together the emotive range of classical Indian music and the expressivity of Indian classical dance to take the audience on India’s journey to freedom and beyond.

From the oppression of the British Raj, to the remarkable stories of the non-violent resistance, led by the heroes of India’s freedom struggle, and carried through with patriotic fervor by the people of the country. From the grief and heartbreak of Partition, to the hope and optimism of present-day India. Waking Up Free is an original Silambam Houston production that celebrates India’s journey to Independence through the centuries-old Indian classical dance form Bharatanatyam.

Silambam Houston was founded in 2002 by Dr. Lavanya Rajagopalan, for the promotion and development of the arts, to impart artistic education, and promote young talent in the performing arts.  Their vision is to increase the appreciation and understanding of Indian artistic traditions across cultural boundaries, through comprehensive arts education, outreach, and exceptional arts programming, and by creating opportunities for young artistes to develop, perform, and collaborate.

All performances at Miller Outdoor Theatre are FREE!

title: Sherlock Holmes
description:
From director Guy Ritchie (Rocknrolla, Lock, Stock and Two Smoking Barrels) comes an all-new take on the classic master detective Sherlock Holmes starring Robert Downey Jr., Jude Law and Rachel McAdams.

Renowned "consulting detective" Sherlock Holmes (Downey Jr.--Iron Man) has a reputation for solving the most complex mysteries. With the aid of his trusted ally Dr. John Watson (Law--The Aviator), Holmes is unequaled in his pursuit of criminals, relying on his singular powers of observation, his remarkable deductive skills -- and the blunt force of his fists. But now a threat unlike anything Holmes has ever confronted threatens London ... and it's just the challenge he's looking for.

After a string of brutal, ritualistic murders, Holmes and Watson arrive just in time to save the latest victim and uncover the killer, the unrepentant Lord Blackwood (Mark Strong--Body of Lies). Before his hanging, Blackwood warns Holmes that death has no power over him, and when Blackwood's apparent resurrection and latest deadly plot panic London and confound Scotland Yard, Holmes and Watson plunge into a world of the dark arts and startling new technologies, where logic is sometimes the best crime-fighting weapon ... but where a good right hook will often do the job.

And the game is afoot!

Academy Award nominations for:
Best Achievement in Art Direction
Best Achievement in Music Written for Motion Pictures, Original Song

More than 2 years after the 2020 presidential election, the small California community of Shasta County terminated its contract with Dominion Voting Systems. They’re the first county in the state to do so. 

Three county supervisors voted to end the contract, despite warnings from the county CEO that it will cost more than $1 million to buy a new voting system and train employees. 

Their argument? That you can’t put a price on voter confidence, so the Dominion systems had to go.

The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' (Dilip Joshi) who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta' (Shailesh Lodha), is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' (Disha Wakani) and a mischievous son 'Tapu' (Bhavya Gandhi / Raj Anadkat). Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalaal' to call his father 'Champaklal' (Amit Bhatt) from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalal.

title: The Murder of Sonic the Hedgehog - Launch Trailer
description:
The Murder of Sonic the Hedgehog is available RIGHT NOW on Steam for FREE!

https://store.steampowered.com/app/2324650/The_Murder_of_Sonic_the_Hedgehog/

It's Amy Rose's birthday and she's hosting a murder mystery party on the Mirage Express! When Sonic the Hedgehog becomes the game's victim, everyone is off to get to the bottom of things. However, something feels a bit off - is this really an innocent game or is something more sinister afoot?

Interrogate some of your favorite characters from the Sonic series as you figure out what happened to Sonic. Play as a new character who is starting their first day working on the Mirage Express, and meet the kind Conductor who is finally retiring from his long run with the train!

This project has been a labor of love from the Sonic Social team and a host of amazingly talented people who are just as passionate about Sonic as we are. Thank you so much for being a part of this with us, and we hope you all enjoy!

Happy April Fool's Day (observed)!
